        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-01T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-01T07:00:00-05:00" n="80" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9–149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-01T13:00:00+01:00">September 1, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 1—10:02 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3503. Embassy’s despatch 1357, August 17, 1949, transmitting documents re China.
                    Re last paragraph despatch under reference, Strang<note n="29" xml:id="d80fn29">Sir William Strang, British Permanent Under Secretary of State for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> has now informed me that policy contained in memorandum
                    dated August 15 from FonOff<note n="30" xml:id="d80fn30">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_57">p. 57</ref>.</note> has
                    been approved by Ministers concerned and can be considered official British
                    policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
